{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"6e2f0406-7439-4ba1-9c75-0d3c33dff544","content":"","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_014pJWHRL7w4zsC2zFh2pEUs","name":"bash","arguments":{"command":"dotnet --version 2>/dev/null && dotnet --list-sdks 2>/dev/null | tail -3","description":"Check .NET SDK version","initial_wait":10},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"Check .NET SDK version"}],"interactionId":"4237ed60-7f07-418c-a1f3-065f520cc7aa","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Now I need to migrate from xUnit.net v2 to xUnit.net v3. Let me identify all the changes needed:\n\n1. **TestProject.csproj**:\n   - Change from `Microsoft.NET.Sdk` to `Microsoft.NET.Sdk` (stays the same, but the project type changes)\n   - In xUnit v3, test projects are executables, not libraries. Need `<OutputType>Exe</OutputType>`.\n   - Remove `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` (not needed in v3)\n   - Replace `xunit` with `xunit.v3` \n   - Remove `xunit.runner.visualstudio` since it's no longer needed in v3; the runner is built into the main package\n   - For `dotnet test` support, the `xunit.v3` package already includes everything required\n   - Test projects become standalone executables with auto-generated entry points, so `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` can be removed as well\n\nNow looking at the `DatabaseSetupAttribute` - in xUnit v3, the `BeforeAfterTestAttribute` has moved to the `Xunit` namespace for attributes, with updated method signatures that take `MethodInfo` and `IXunitTest` parameters instead of the older approach. The `Before` and `After` methods now take both the method info and the test instance as parameters instead of just the method. I should verify the exact signatures by checking the actual package, and I'm also noticing that the test runner configuration in global.json might need adjustment for xUnit v3 compatibility with the newer .NET versions. xUnit v3 is built around Microsoft.Testing.Platform rather than VSTest, so I need to configure global.json accordingly for `dotnet test` to work properly on .NET 8. My migration plan involves converting the test project to an executable by adding the appropriate output type, swapping out the old xUnit packages for xUnit v3, and then updating the test attributes to work with the new framework.\n\nLet me start implementing these changes and see what compilation errors surface, then check which .NET SDK version is available.","outputTokens":1758,"requestId":"1BC7:29DEC0:781D10:8826CD:6A03E101"},"id":"3d8813e2-cc8a-478a-9926-7642d1655cc1","timestamp":"2026-05-13T02:25:38.442Z","parentId":"ba22a452-7dfa-410e-9098-1f17d5791bbc"}
